trans-unit.source: The default extension of the <xref href="System.Web.Configuration.HttpCapabilitiesProvider"></xref> class that is included with ASP.NET.
Initializes a new instance of the <xref href="System.Web.Configuration.HttpCapabilitiesDefaultProvider"></xref> class.
Initializes a new instance of the <xref href="System.Web.Configuration.HttpCapabilitiesDefaultProvider"></xref> class with the values of the specified instance.
The <xref href="System.Web.Configuration.HttpCapabilitiesDefaultProvider"></xref> instance to use for initializing a new instance.
Adds an HTTP request string to use to parse browser capability information.
This method adds to the collection that is created by the `use` child element of the `browserCaps` element of the Web.config file.
The string to use to parse browser capability information.
Adds a search string that modifies a browser definition.
This method adds to the collection that is created by the `filter` child element of the `browserCaps` element of the Web.config file.
The search string that modifies a browser definition.
Gets or sets the length of time in seconds to retain the <xref href="System.Web.HttpBrowserCapabilities"></xref> object in the cache.
The length of time in seconds to retain the <xref href="System.Web.HttpBrowserCapabilities"></xref> object in the cache.
Gets the <xref href="System.Web.HttpBrowserCapabilities"></xref> object for the specified <xref href="System.Web.HttpRequest"></xref> object.
The <xref href="System.Web.HttpRequest"></xref> object.
The <xref href="System.Web.HttpBrowserCapabilities"></xref> object for the <xref href="System.Web.HttpRequest"></xref> object that was passed in.
Gets or sets the type of the class that is used to hold the results from parsing the <xref uid="langword_csharp_browserCap" name="browserCap" href=""></xref> element of the Web.config file.
This property corresponds to the `result` child element of the `browserCaps` element of the Web.config file.
The type of the class that is used to hold the results from parsing the <xref uid="langword_csharp_browserCaps" name="browserCaps" href=""></xref> element of the Web.config file.
Gets or sets the number of characters from the user agent string to use for caching of the <xref href="System.Web.HttpBrowserCapabilities"></xref> object.
The number of characters from the supplied user agent string to use for caching of the <xref href="System.Web.HttpBrowserCapabilities"></xref> object.
